<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3995353>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Details of male specimens of Macrogomphus phalantus: a–f—M. p. jayavarman subsp; nov., the holotype; gh—M. p. phalantus (After Lieftinck 1935: figs.11–12); a—head, frontal view; b–c,g—secondary genitalia, lateral view; d—anal appendages, dorsal view; e—ditto, lateral view; f—ditto, ventral view; h—dorsal and lateral view. Scale bar 1 mm. Asterisk indicates the proximal inner swellings of the cerci." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3995353/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3995347>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Holotype, male (a), and paratype, female (b) of Macrogomphus phalantus jayavarman subsp; nov. Cambodia, Siem Reap Province, 1.5 km SSW of Kampong Pluk village, 70 m S from northern bank of Lake Tonlé Sap, low, open temporarily flooded forest, 13.1956° N, 103.9725° E, 3 m a.s.l., 15 vi 2018, O. Kosterin leg." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3995347/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3995349>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. A male paratype of Macrogomphus phalantus jayavarman subsp; nov. in live colours (the same data as in Fig. 9)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3995349/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3995355>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Details of the female paratype of Macrogomphus phalantus jayavarman subsp; nov., the holotype; a—head, frontal view; b—occiput, frontal view; d—right part of vulvar lamina, ventral view. Scale bar 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3995355/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3995351>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Males of Macrogomphus phalantus jayavarman subsp; nov. in nature (the same data as in Fig. 9). On the left upper photo a dead colony of bivalve mollusks is seen on the branch, which appeared when the forest was inundated." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3995351/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3995327>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Details of some male specimens of Macrogomphus albardae kept in RMNH (courtesy of Jan van Tol): a–d—the male syntype (the labels ‘Holotype’ are misleading); e—“W. Borneo, 0 m. / Singkawang / Penanring / L. Coomans de Ruiter / 24. II. 1932”; f—“S. Sumatra / Terbanggi-Hilir / nr. Menggala / Lampang distr. / 18. VIII. 1936 / M. Bartels”; a—general habitus; b, e–f—S10 and anal appendages, dorsal view; c—head and thorax, dorsolateral view; d—labels of the male syntype. Not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3995327/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3995333>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. A small male of Macrogomphus albardae of the ringed morph, collected by the author on 21 viii 2018 in Cambodia, Preah Vihear Province, Srae Veal village env.: a—habitus in live colours, dorsal view; b—ditto, lateral view (not to scale); canal appendages, dorsal view; d—ditto, lateral view; e—secondary genitalia, lateral view; f—posterior hamulus, anteriolateral view. Scale bars: upper 2 mm; lower 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3995333/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3995357>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Habitat of Macrogomphus phalantus jayavarman subsp; nov., margin of open temporarily flooded forest 1.5 km SSW of Kampong Pluk village, 70 m S from northern bank of Lake Tonlé Sap, at the beginning of water level rise on 15 vi 2018." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3995357/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

